    <node id="CONTENT">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT</data>
      <data key="d1">The **CONTENT** entity is a dimension table designed to store detailed information about various pieces of content, such as movies and shows, to support analytical processes like content performance evaluation and popularity analysis. It serves as a centralized reference for attributes including a unique identifier (`content_id`), the content's title, genre, and distributor. The table is structured to enable granular analysis of content success metrics, leveraging its unique identifiers to link with related datasets (e.g., viewership or engagement facts). While both descriptions emphasize its role in performance analysis, the inclusion of "distributor" and explicit references to "popularity analysis" in the first description enriches the scope, suggesting the table also supports insights into content distribution strategies and audience reception trends. The combined view presents a cohesive structure optimized for multidimensional reporting and decision-making in content management.</data>
      <data key="d2">7446f3bdab43b104430ec67356fd7051,ec58eb007760aac2843ddf10b7ac617a</data>
      <data key="d3">1</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
      <data key="d5">10</data>
      <data key="d6">3</data>
      <data key="d7">077d2820ae1845bcbb1803379a3d1eae</data>
    </node>
