    </node>
    <node id="CONTENT_ID">
      <data key="d0">ATTRIBUTE</data>
      <data key="d1">The **CONTENT_ID** serves as both the **Primary Key** in the content table, uniquely identifying each content item (e.g., programs, videos), and as a **Foreign Key** in streaming event tables to link interactions (e.g., views, plays) to their corresponding content. It is central to relational integrity, enabling cross-table joins for analytics and reporting. The identifier has aliases like **program_id** and **video_id**, reflecting its application across diverse content types within the system. This dual role ensures traceability of content consumption while maintaining a standardized reference for metadata, such as titles, genres, or durations, stored in the content table.</data>
      <data key="d2">7446f3bdab43b104430ec67356fd7051,ec58eb007760aac2843ddf10b7ac617a</data>
      <data key="d3">2</data>
      <data key="d4">0</data>
