    <node id="CATALOG">
      <data key="d0">CONCEPT</data>
      <data key="d1">The **CATALOG** entity serves as an alias for the **content table**, specifically representing Netflix's available media library. It acts as an alternative reference to streamline interactions with the underlying data structure, enabling simplified querying or contextual clarity in database operations. Both descriptions confirm its role as a secondary identifier for the content table, emphasizing its purpose in abstracting or standardizing access to Netflix's media inventory within a data architecture. No contradictions exist between the descriptions, as they collectively reinforce its functional and referential utility.</data>
      <data key="d2">7446f3bdab43b104430ec67356fd7051,ec58eb007760aac2843ddf10b7ac617a</data>
