    <edge source="CONTENT" target="CATALOG">
      <data key="d8">8.0</data>
      <data key="d9">The **CONTENT** entity is structured as a table within the data model, and the **CATALOG** entity serves as a direct alias for this table. Both provided descriptions explicitly confirm that "Catalog" (or "catalog," indicating case insensitivity in this context) is synonymous with the **CONTENT** table, establishing a one-to-one relationship between the two entities. This alias relationship implies that queries or references to **CATALOG** will interact with the underlying **CONTENT** table, ensuring consistency in data access and manipulation. No contradictions exist between the descriptions, as both uniformly define **CATALOG** as an alternative identifier for the **CONTENT** table.</data>
      <data key="d10">7446f3bdab43b104430ec67356fd7051,ec58eb007760aac2843ddf10b7ac617a</data>
      <data key="d11">ef32c4b208d041cc856f6837915dc1b0</data>
